---------------------------------------------------------------------------
Create:  (POST)

"/api/v1/assignment/"

    -Give it an assignment JSON and it will write it to a file with the id as its name.
    -Returns 'success' or 'file already exists'

---------------------------------------------------------------------------
Read:  (GET)

"/api/v1/assignment/:id.json"

    -Replace :id with the actual id #
    -Ex: "/api/v1/assignment/003.json"
    -Returns a JSON object of the assignment with the matching id

---------------------------------------------------------------------------
Update:  (PUT)

"/api/v1/assignment/:id.json"

    -Give it an assignment JSON and it will write it to the file system
    -Replace :id with the actual id #
    -Ex: "/api/v1/assignment/003.json"
    -Returns JSON object it wrote to file

---------------------------------------------------------------------------
Delete:  (DELETE)

"/api/v1/assignment/:id.json"

    -Deletes file with the id you give it
    -Replace :id with the actual id #
    -Ex: "/api/v1/assignment/003.json"
    -Returns 'deleted' or 'error'

---------------------------------------------------------------------------
List:  (GET)

"/api/v1/assignments.json"
    
    -Returns list of all fileNames in the assignments folder
    
---------------------------------------------------------------------------